00:05.280 --> 00:11.220
We are already learnt how to select data from the database and how to insert data into the database

00:11.520 --> 00:16.470
using keywell to update data that are already in the database.

00:16.500 --> 00:18.760
We use the update statement.

00:22.370 --> 00:29.270
We start an update statement in esky well with the stop date key word followed by the name of the table.

00:30.140 --> 00:36.900
Then we add the set word followed by a column name and the value we want to set it to.

00:37.640 --> 00:44.450
We can update several columns in one statement by listing several columns and then new values separated

00:44.450 --> 00:46.940
by commas.

00:46.950 --> 00:53.990
Finally we optionally add a weather condition to only update records that match this condition.

00:53.990 --> 01:00.110
This condition is specified in the same way we add conditions to a select statement.

